12/05/2009
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Prime Minister Nikola Spiric accepted the resignation Monday (May 11th) of Transport and Communications Minister Bozo Ljubic, who stepped down for personal reasons. As a leader of the ruling coalition partner Croatian Democratic Union-1990 (HDZ-1990), Ljubic proposed party deputy chairman Rudo Vidovic as his successor in the ministry post. Parliament must confirm Vidovic's appointment.
In other news, the State Information and Protection Agency (SIPA) arrested three Serbian citizens Sunday with counterfeit money on them. Police officers found about 80,000 euros with the suspects in Sarajevo. The operation leading up to the arrests spanned several months. (Dnevni Avaz, RTRS, SRNA, BHRT, Tanjug - 11/05/09)
